   ## Features Implemented in Increment 2

   ### Tag System
   - **Tag Creation:** Create tags with auto-assigned colors from a sophisticated palette
   - **Tag Management:** Add, remove, and manage tags on individual tasks
   - **Workspace Tags:** Tags are saved at the workspace level for reuse across tasks
   - **Visual Display:** Tags are displayed with color-coded labels on task cards

   ### Search Functionality
   - **Global Search:** Search bar in sidebar searches across all pages, tasks, notes, and tags
   - **Real-time Results:** Press Enter to see search results with clickable navigation
   - **Search Result Types:** Results show the type (Page, Task, Note, Tag) and location
   - **Keyboard Support:** Press Escape to clear search

   ### Task Filtering
   - **Status Filter:** Filter tasks by Not Started, In Progress, Completed, or Cancelled
   - **Priority Filter:** Filter tasks by High, Medium, or Low priority
   - **Clear Filters:** One-click button to reset all filters
   - **Dynamic Updates:** Filters apply instantly without page refresh

   ### Dark Mode
   - **Theme Toggle:** Switch between light and dark themes from the sidebar
   - **Full UI Theming:** All colors adapt including backgrounds, text, borders, and cards
   - **Persistent Setting:** Dark mode preference is saved with workspace data
   - **Smooth Transition:** UI rebuilds seamlessly when toggling themes

   ### Task Due Date Reminders
   - **Visual Alerts:** Tasks due within 3 days are highlighted with a warning background color
   - **Due Soon Indicator:** Shows "Due in X days" for approaching deadlines
   - **Today Indicator:** Tasks due today are prominently marked
   - **Overdue Styling:** Overdue tasks have distinct red-tinted background

   ### Archive Pages
   - **Archive Button:** Archive pages to hide them from the main view
   - **Archived View:** Dedicated view in sidebar to see all archived pages
   - **Restore Pages:** Restore archived pages back to the main workspace
   - **Permanent Delete:** Option to permanently delete archived pages

   ### Export/Import
   - **Export Workspace:** Save entire workspace to a JSON file for backup
   - **Import Workspace:** Load workspace data from a JSON backup file
   - **File Chooser:** Standard file dialogs for selecting save/load locations
   - **Confirmation Dialog:** Warning before import overwrites current data

